- Why should we use functions at all?
we use funtion to automate the repetative tasks that involve the same parameters and return the same type of result under same calculation process.
This will save your time/energy/neuron/batery...

- How to define/declare a function?
text def + name of the function (parameters)

- How to call/use a function?
text the name of the function along with specific value of its parameters

- What is return, why and how do we use it?
return is the output of the funtion after it process the input (parameters). we can use the result (return) for what ever purpose if it is applicable.

- Do we have to use return in every function?
Not necessarily

- What are function arguments/parameters, why and how we use it?
They are the input of the function, we give them specific value and we wil get specific result.

- How to use function from a different file other than our currently working file?
from name_of_local_file_that_contains_the_function import * or import function
name_of_local_file_that_contains_the_function.function(parameters)